\begin_layout Standard
Wearable computational devices are more accessible and more popular than
 ever.
 These devices are personal and are embeded with physiological sensors.
 The most current use of these sensors are health monitoring.
 For example, runners have access to their hearthbeat, their traveled distances,
 their itinerary, etc.
 Physiological sensors measure something deeply personal while at the same
 time measuring information that is not explicitely available to us.
 For example, what is happening in my brain right now? How stressed am I?
 Indeed, for many of the emotional states we are going through on a daily
 basis, the body react way before the mind realize what is going on [REF].
 For example, how useful would it be to realize that you are experiencing
 impatience before acting impatient with your spouse? Health monitoring
 is popular exactly because people are not explicitely and objectively aware
 of how well their body is doing.
